DA Free State Leadership Election Results 14 November 2020 eval(ez_write_tag([[300,250],'politicsweb_co_za-box-3','ezslot_0',112,'0','0']));We are delighted to announce the results of the Leadership Elections which took place at the Democratic Alliance (DA) Free State elective Congress 2020. Voting for Leadership Candidates took place using the online OpaVote platform and this system worked well. The election results were compliant with all DA election requirements and rules. They were signed off by us, as presiding officers, as well as the candidates' party agents and also a professional audit firm who acted as independent external auditors and who oversaw the voting process. All individuals who observed voting consider the elections free and fair. eval(ez_write_tag([[580,400],'politicsweb_co_za-medrectangle-3','ezslot_1',113,'0','0']));The results of the elections are as follows: Provincial Leader: Dr Roy Jankielsohn Provincial Chairperson:eval(ez_write_tag([[580,400],'politicsweb_co_za-medrectangle-4','ezslot_2',114,'0','0'])); Werner Horn Deputy Provincial Chairperson: eval(ez_write_tag([[336,280],'politicsweb_co_za-box-4','ezslot_4',115,'0','0']));Carina Serfontein Provincial Finance Chairperson: David van Vuuren We extend our congratulations to all duly elected candidates. The DA now enters an exciting new chapter and will deliver real hope and real change to the people of South Africa, now. Issued by Greg Krumbock MP - DA Free State Provincial Congress Presiding Officer, 14 November 2020